COVID19 has created the worst situation in the entire nation Daily more than 65 thousand

cases are increasing at an exponential rate

More than 28 lakh students will be giving JEE and NEI

of which many students live

in joint family with senior citizens or infants If exams get conducted then the student can

become a carrier of the virus if they come in contact with an infected person

There are many asymptomatic cases who will attend the exam which cant be stopped

and exposure of such students to others will increase contraction

Other than COVID19 many parts of Bihar state is suffering with floods and no state

transport is available in those areas and students will not be able to reach exam centres which

are at distance of 300400km for many students 50000 applicants will attend NEET exam in

Bihar and only two centres are allotted there which will create crowd situation at centre

SOPs are provided by the government for the exams which have many flaws and

in Karnataka and KCET exam in Kerala

A practical issue is seen for spectacle wearing students if they wear mask fog is

generated on specs making them difficult to concentrate on the exam

SC stated postponement will put students career in jeopardy ironically in video
